## v2.2.0 (2026-06-13) -- Salvage commit-msg-stage hooks learning (closed PR #2353)

**Source:** Closed PR #2353 (HomericIntelligence/ProjectMnemosyne) — commit-msg-stage hooks
and `default_install_hook_types` learning that was dropped when the PR was closed without merge.

**What changed:**

- Added triggers (17) and (18) to `description` and `When to Use`:
  (17) adding a commit-msg-stage hook — must set `default_install_hook_types: [pre-commit, commit-msg]`
  or plain `pre-commit install` silently omits the commit-msg stage;
  (18) verifying a commit-msg hook — `--all-files` does NOT run commit-msg-stage hooks; use
  `pre-commit run --hook-stage commit-msg --commit-msg-filename <file>`.
- Added new Quick Reference block for commit-msg-stage hooks in the `### Quick Reference` section.
- Added new detailed subsection `#### commit-msg-stage hooks and \`default_install_hook_types\``
  under the main Verified Workflow covering:
  - Root cause of silent-inert hook pattern (missing `default_install_hook_types`)
  - The canonical fix (one-line at top of `.pre-commit-config.yaml`)
  - How to verify the hook fires (`--hook-stage commit-msg --commit-msg-filename`)
  - Commit-msg validator hook YAML pattern (`language: system`, `pass_filenames: true`)
  - Ruff D301 raw-docstring fix for validator scripts containing `\n` escape sequences
  - "Your pre-commit configuration is unstaged" abort and how to avoid it
  - `core.hooksPath` note: blocked `install` does NOT block `--hook-stage` verification
- Added 5 new `Failed Attempts` rows:
  1. Inert commit-msg hook under plain install (no `default_install_hook_types`)
  2. Verified commit-msg hook with `--all-files` and shipped an untested/inert hook
  3. Ruff D301 — bare docstring with `\n` in validator script
  4. "Pre-commit configuration is unstaged" abort during `--hook-stage` run
  5. Assumed `core.hooksPath`-blocked install also blocks `--hook-stage` verification
- Added `commit-msg` and `default-install-hook-types` to `tags`.
- Added ProjectMnemosyne row to Verified On table.

**Key new verified facts (from closed PR #2353):**

- `default_install_hook_types` must be set explicitly; default covers only `pre-commit` stage
- `pre-commit run --all-files` is stage-blind: commit-msg-stage hooks are silently skipped
- Canonical verification: `pre-commit run --hook-stage commit-msg --commit-msg-filename <file>`
- `language: system` + `pass_filenames: true` is the correct pattern for commit-msg validators
- `core.hooksPath` blocking install does NOT block `--hook-stage` framework invocation

**Verification level:** verified — from closed PR #2353 development session

