## v1.8.0 (2026-06-07) -- Absorb 4 lint/quality skills (ruff-format trap, PR-diff scope, editorconfig, toolchain-churn review exemption)

Consolidated 4 overlapping skills into this canonical (LQ05 cluster):

- `tooling-ruff-format-precommit-check-trap` — `ruff check` vs `ruff format` are SEPARATE tools sharing one binary; pre-push 4-command sequence.
- `precommit-scope-full-pr-diff-not-current-edit` — run pre-commit against the full PR diff (`--from-ref/--to-ref`), not just `--files <current edit>`; sub-agent commit coverage.
- `tooling-editorconfig-cross-editor-consistency` — add `.editorconfig` for cross-editor formatting on non-Python files.
- `review-rubric-exempt-toolchain-forced-churn` — exempt toolchain-forced incidental churn from PR-review scope/YAGNI rubrics (intent-based carve-out).

Each absorbed skill's original frontmatter and full body are preserved verbatim below under `## Superseded from <name>`.

## v1.6.0 (2026-06-07) -- Add ruff B904 raise-from and C901 complexity fix patterns

**Changed by:** PR #2012 (skill/pre-commit-ruff-mypy-fixes) rebased onto main v1.5.0
**Verification:** verified-local (pre-commit + pytest pass; CI pending)

### What changed

- Added 2 new "When to Use" triggers: B904 (`raise ... from err` in `except` clause) and C901 (`main` is too complex)
- Added 2 new Failed Attempts rows: bare `raise` inside `except ImportError`, and over-complex `main()` at C901 complexity 17

### Why

PR #643 (coverage floor + e2e backstop) failed pre-commit after rebasing onto new main that added Bandit SAST. Two of the remaining lint issues — B904 bare raise-in-except and an over-complex `main()` (C901) — were not yet captured in the canonical skill. B904 has no auto-fix and requires chaining the cause with `raise ... from err`; C901 requires extracting helpers so each has complexity ≤10. These findings are layered on top of main's v1.5.0 (which already had the I001/RUF059, untracked-mypy, pixi-shadowing, and bandit findings).

